olive oil
1 carrot
2 potato
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 packet lamb rump
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot and potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray, then sprinkle with garlic & herb seasoning and drizzle with olive oil.
• Toss to coat and season with salt and pepper. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, add shredded cabbage mix, baby spinach leaves, 1/2 the dill & parsley mayonnaise and a drizzle of olive oil. Season and toss to coat. Set aside.
• Lightly score lamb fat in a criss-cross pattern.
• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if you're sensitive to heat! In a second medium bowl, combine Louisiana spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Add lamb rump, season and turn to coat.

Little cooks: Help combine the ingredients for the slaw

• When veggies have 12 minutes remaining, place lamb, fat-side down, in a large frying pan (no need for oil!). Place pan over medium heat and cook, undisturbed, until golden, 10-12 minutes.
• Increase heat to high and sear lamb rump on all sides for 30 seconds.
• Transfer lamb, fat-side up, to a lined oven tray. Roast for 15-20 minutes for medium or until cooked to your liking.
• Remove lamb from the oven, cover with foil and set aside to rest for 10 minutes.

• Slice Louisiana baked lamb rump.
• Divide herb-roasted veggies, slaw and lamb between plates.
• Serve with a dollop of remaining dill-parsley mayo. Enjoy!